<section>
Basic definitions

If there is an edge between two vertices, we say they are adjacent.

The degree of the vertex is the number of edges incident to it.

</section>

<section>
<p>Two features that are sometimes not allowed </p>
<ul>
<li> A vertex can have a loop -- an edge connecting it to itself </li>
<li> There could be multiple edges between the same two vertices </li>
<ul>
<p> Graphs without these two features are called simple.

</section>


<section>
A subgraph $S$ of $\Gamma$ consists of a subset of vertices and a subset of the edges.

We require the vertices at the end of each edges of $S$ to be in $S$.

</section>


<section>
<image src="Pictures/InstantInsanityPackage.JPG"></image>
</section>

<section>
<h1> Instant Insanity </h1>
<ul>
<li> 4 cubes </li>
<li>Each side of each cube is colored one of four colors</li>
<li>Goal is to stack the cubes so each direction has one face of each color</li>
</ul>
</section>

			



